Here is a non-rhyming poem:

Silence falls like a soft mist 
enveloping the city in its gentle grasp 
the sounds of humanity muffled and distant 
as if heard through a thick veil 

In this quiet world time stands still 
no clock ticks no bird sings 
only the beat of my heart echoes through the emptiness 
a reminder that I am alive 

The darkness presses in around me 
a physical presence that cannot be ignored 
it seeps into my bones chilling me to the marrow 
leaving me feeling fragile and vulnerable 

And yet in this bleakness I find solace 
a strange sense of comfort in the desolation 
perhaps it's the freedom from expectation 
or the simplicity of being alone 

Whatever the reason it's enough for now 
to let the silence wash over me 
and carry away my doubts and fears on its gentle tide.assistant

I hope you enjoy the poem!
